<doc id="86628" wikidata="Q7205116" url="?curid=86628" title="Plor na mBan">
<text>In Irish mythology, Plúr na mBan (pronounced &quot;ploor-nu-mon&quot;)—meaning &quot;the flower of women&quot;—was the daughter of Oisín and Niamh.

==References==</text><links>
<link wikidata="Q1471505" start="3" end="18" title="Irish mythology" label="Irish mythology"/>
<link wikidata="Q7205116" start="20" end="32" title="Plor na mBan" label="Plúr na mBan"/>
